00:03:05.650 --> 00:03:07.830
-I think the reason
for the DNA symposium

00:03:07.830 --> 00:03:10.160
was just the
incredible development

00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:15.040
in the last several years, the
last decade, of DNA science,

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:19.150
of synthetic biology, of
really exploding information

00:03:19.150 --> 00:03:22.100
about our ancestry
and our origins that

00:03:22.100 --> 00:03:23.957
are revealed by DNA analysis.

00:03:23.957 --> 00:03:25.790
And we thought, wow,
what an exciting moment

00:03:25.790 --> 00:03:27.620
to bring it all together.

00:03:27.620 --> 00:03:29.604
-This technology
is new, very new.

00:03:29.604 --> 00:03:31.270
And so in addition
to the science, today

00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:34.430
we'll be discussing the ethical
aspects of this new world.

00:03:34.430 --> 00:03:35.940
-We had anthropologists.

00:03:35.940 --> 00:03:38.340
We had evolutionary biologists.

00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:40.190
We had chemists.

00:03:40.190 --> 00:03:42.200
We had criminal justice.

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:44.390
We had an ethicist.

00:03:44.390 --> 00:03:46.730
-They brought together
different areas of research

00:03:46.730 --> 00:03:50.250
that I am interested
in, but might not have

00:03:50.250 --> 00:03:52.870
talked to in the same room.

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:54.150
-Today's been incredible.

00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:56.240
It's a great opportunity
to hear about research

00:03:56.240 --> 00:03:59.291
from around the world in a
completely interdisciplinary

00:03:59.291 --> 00:03:59.790
way.

00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:02.840
So you get totally outside of
your specific little bubble

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:04.530
that you study.

00:04:04.530 --> 00:04:09.210
-But I also think bringing it
to the public is absolutely key.

00:04:09.210 --> 00:04:12.120
This stuff has enormous
ethical implications.

00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:14.730
It has enormous implications
for human health.

00:04:14.730 --> 00:04:18.550
It has big implications
for how we see ourselves.

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:22.620
And that can only be addressed
in an interdisciplinary setting

00:04:22.620 --> 00:04:23.747
like Radcliffe.

