00:04:28.220 --> 00:04:30.890
-We have the world's
leading collection

00:04:30.890 --> 00:04:34.870
of materials around
women's rights movements,

00:04:34.870 --> 00:04:39.310
from the first stirrings of
such movements in the 1830s

00:04:39.310 --> 00:04:42.900
and 1840s, through what we
call second wave feminism,

00:04:42.900 --> 00:04:45.120
and on into today.

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:48.050
Bill Baird was a
really important player

00:04:48.050 --> 00:04:52.860
in the reproductive rights
pieces of those movements.

00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:55.230
The Bill Baird collection
is the largest collection

00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:57.780
a library has ever acquired.

00:04:57.780 --> 00:05:02.230
700 plus boxes came out
of Mr. Baird's basement.

00:05:02.230 --> 00:05:05.560
One of the things that was
carted out of his basement

00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:09.630
was a carton of
badly burned books.

00:05:09.630 --> 00:05:12.630
The first act of domestic
terrorism against an abortion

00:05:12.630 --> 00:05:14.750
provider was leveled
against Baird.

00:05:14.750 --> 00:05:17.520
His offices were firebombed.

00:05:17.520 --> 00:05:20.140
It's going to be
important, in 100 years,

00:05:20.140 --> 00:05:24.720
literally to demonstrate
the heat of this argument.

00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:28.860
I think one of the truly
remarkable things about Baird

00:05:28.860 --> 00:05:33.820
is that he treated his
opponents in the Right to Life

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:39.100
movement with enough seriousness
to collect their materials.

00:05:39.100 --> 00:05:42.590
Having the pro-life materials,
the anti-choice materials

00:05:42.590 --> 00:05:46.740
in the Baird collection, I think
is really of inestimable value.

00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:50.135
